  "title": "Asking about times and appointments",
  "dialect": "darija",
  "steps": [
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking 'What time is it?'"
        },
        "text": "To ask about the current time in Darija, you use the phrase 'شحال فالساعة؟'. This literally translates to 'How much in the hour?' but is understood as 'What time is it?'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "شحال فالساعة؟",
            "english": "What time is it?",
            "transliteration": "ShHal fess-sa'a?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "شحال فالساعة دابا؟",
            "english": "What time is it now?",
            "transliteration": "ShHal fess-sa'a daba?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Telling the Hour: 1 to 6 o'clock"
        },
        "text": "When telling time, you typically say 'الساعة' (ess-sa'a) followed by the hour. Here are the hours from 1 to 6:",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "الساعة الوحدة",
            "english": "One o'clock",
            "transliteration": "Ess-sa'a l-weHda"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "الساعة الجوج",
            "english": "Two o'clock",
            "transliteration": "Ess-sa'a j-jūj"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "الساعة التلاتة",
            "english": "Three o'clock",
            "transliteration": "Ess-sa'a t-tlāta"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "الساعة الربعة",
            "english": "Four o'clock",
            "transliteration": "Ess-sa'a r-reb'a"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "الساعة الخمسة",
            "english": "Five o'clock",
            "transliteration": "Ess-sa'a l-khemsa"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "الساعة الستة",
            "english": "Six o'clock",
            "transliteration": "Ess-sa'a s-setta"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Telling the Hour: 7 to 12 o'clock"
        },
        "text": "Continuing with the hours, here are 7 to 12:",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "الساعة السبعة",
            "english": "Seven o'clock",
            "transliteration": "Ess-sa'a s-seb'a"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "الساعة التمانية",
            "english": "Eight o'clock",
            "transliteration": "Ess-sa'a t-tmenya"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "الساعة التسعود",
            "english": "Nine o'clock",
            "transliteration": "Ess-sa'a t-tes'ūd"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "الساعة العشرة",
            "english": "Ten o'clock",
            "transliteration": "Ess-sa'a l-'ashra"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "الساعة الحداش",
            "english": "Eleven o'clock",
            "transliteration": "Ess-sa'a l-Hdash"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "الساعة التناش",
            "english": "Twelve o'clock",
            "transliteration": "Ess-sa'a t-tnash"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
