    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "The Word for 'Appointment'"
        },
        "text": "The word for 'appointment' in Darija is 'موعد' (maw'id). It's a masculine noun.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "عندي موعد مع الطبيب.",
            "english": "I have an appointment with the doctor.",
            "transliteration": "'Andi maw'id m'a t-tbib."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "واش عندك شي موعد؟",
            "english": "Do you have an appointment?",
            "transliteration": "Wash 'andek shi maw'id?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking 'When?'"
        },
        "text": "To ask 'When?' in Darija, you can use 'إيمتا؟' (imta?) or 'وقتاش؟' (weqtash?). Both are common.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "إيمتا الموعد؟",
            "english": "When is the appointment?",
            "transliteration": "Imta l-maw'id?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "وقتاش غادين نمشيو؟",
            "english": "When are we going to go?",
            "transliteration": "Weqtash ghādin nemshiw?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking if Someone is Free"
        },
        "text": "To ask if someone is free or available, you use 'واش مسالي؟' (wash msali?) for a male and 'واش مسالية؟' (wash msaliya?) for a female. You can also ask 'واش عندك الوقت؟' (wash 'andek l-weqt?) meaning 'Do you have time?'",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "واش نتا مسالي غدا؟",
            "english": "Are you (male) free tomorrow?",
            "transliteration": "Wash nta msālī ghadda?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "واش نتي مسالية اليوم؟",
            "english": "Are you (female) free today?",
            "transliteration": "Wash nti msālīya l-yūm?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "واش عندك الوقت لعشية؟",
            "english": "Do you have time this afternoon?",
            "transliteration": "Wash 'andek l-weqt l-'ashiya?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
