    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Suggesting a Time: 'How about...?'"
        },
        "text": "To suggest a time or ask someone's opinion on a proposed time, you can use 'كيف جاك...؟' (kif jā-k...?) which means 'How did it seem to you...?' or 'What do you think of...?', or more directly 'واش كاين...' (wash kāin...) which means 'Is there...?' or 'Is it possible...?'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "كيف جاتك الساعة الخمسة؟",
            "english": "How about five o'clock?",
            "transliteration": "Kif jātek ess-sa'a l-khemsa?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "واش كاين الموعد مع الربعة؟",
            "english": "How about an appointment at four?",
            "transliteration": "Wash kāin l-maw'id m'a r-reb'a?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking 'Is it convenient/possible?'"
        },
        "text": "To ask if a time is convenient or suitable, you can say 'واش مناسب؟' (wash mnāseb?) for masculine or 'واش مناسبة؟' (wash mnāseba?) for feminine. For 'Is it possible?', use 'واش ممكن؟' (wash mumkin?).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "واش هاد الوقت مناسب ليك؟",
            "english": "Is this time convenient for you (m.)?",
            "transliteration": "Wash hād l-weqt mnāseb līk?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "واش ممكن نتلاقاو غدا؟",
            "english": "Is it possible for us to meet tomorrow?",
            "transliteration": "Wash mumkin n-tlāqāw ghadda?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Confirming an Appointment"
        },
        "text": "To confirm, you can use simple affirmations like 'صافي' (safi) meaning 'okay/done/agreed', 'واخا' (wākha) meaning 'okay', or 'مزيان' (mzyān) meaning 'good/fine'. You can also say 'تمام' (tamām) for 'perfect'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "صافي، نشوفوك ديك الساعة.",
            "english": "Okay, see you then.",
            "transliteration": "Sāfi, n-shūfūk dik ess-sa'a."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "واخا، غادي نكون تما.",
            "english": "Okay, I'll be there.",
            "transliteration": "Wākha, ghādi nkūn tamma."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
